OPML Parser
=======================================================================================================================

What is OPML?
=>>>>
OPML (Outline Processor Markup Language) is an XML format for outlines (defined as "a tree, where each node contains a set of named attributes with string values"). Originally developed by Radio UserLand as a native file format for an outliner application, it has since been adopted for other uses, the most common being to exchange lists of web feeds between web feed aggregators.

=========================================

OPML Parser
=>>>>>
This parses any OPML file and generates a human-readable html file. This can be used display the html formatted opml by the web feeds. This script takes the .opml file as the input and outputs a html for the same in a different file.

=========================================

Usage
=>>>>>
Run the php script sc4.php with the input opml file as the argument.

            ./sc4.php <the opml filename>  //  .sc4.php example.opml
            
       and a file output.html will be generated containing the html format.
========================================================================================================================== 
